<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-16997] Handle timestamp wraparound for internode messages</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16997</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In internode messaging we send the lower 4 bytes of the timestamp and then correct on receiving side if the local time has wrapped (every 50 days), but we currently don&apos;t correct the time if the sending side wrapped before us. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can cause us to use the wrong timestamp for the message and if the local System.nanoTime is &amp;lt; 50 days, we get a negative creation time which causes an AssertionError in MonitorableImpl&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
